(1649, 654, 'case_transaction', 'The transaction, completed in late 2015, allowed management to retain a significant ownership stake post-transaction. This transaction also allowed the previous institutional private equity investors to exit their investment in Alpha. \r\n'),
(1650, 654, '_case_transaction', 'field_523879cf25b62'),
(1651, 654, 'case_opportunity', 'Alpha is the largest value added distribution and service partner for the leading manufacturer of women’s medical imaging equipment in the United States. Alpha’s exclusive OEM relationships provide Alpha with the opportunity to deliver value-added sales processing, distribution, installation and service support to a wide variety of healthcare facility networks. The Company’s strong customer relationships, in turn, uniquely position Alpha as a necessary and trusted distribution and service partner for each OEM. Alpha has service contracts that provide recurring contractual future revenue for the term of the contracts, which we have worked with the Company to improve. '),
(1652, 654, '_case_opportunity', 'field_52387ac4deac3'),
(1653, 654, 'case_strategy', 'We worked with Alpha to establish a short and long-term plan to grow their business in new geographies and expand into secondary markets with weaker penetration. We continue to work with management to find add-on acquisitions to expand the Company’s product mix and geographic coverage.\r\n'),
(1654, 654, '_case_strategy', 'field_52387b3915786'),
