(153, 1, '2013-09-23 16:29:41', '2013-09-23 16:29:41', '<p>Geoff Faux, a co-founder and Managing Partner of Caymus Equity, has over 30 years of private equity investing, senior executive, and financial experience focused on the lower middle market. Geoff has extensive experience in acquisitions, mergers, and operations, and he has assisted numerous management teams in achieving their growth potential. Geoff’s expertise includes leading numerous transactions, growing existing platform companies, working with successful management teams, and attracting key executives.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2001, Geoff was the founder of Caymus Partners LLC, a merchant banking firm focused on financial advisory and principal investing exclusively in the lower middle market in a variety of industry segments including business services, healthcare services, and consumer and niche manufacturing. In 2009, Geoff was the co-founder of Caymus Equity Partners LLC, which was formed to be the exclusive private equity investing vehicle for Caymus Partners.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prior to founding Caymus Partners, Geoff was a senior executive of Orthodontic Centers of America, Inc. (“OCA”), a former New York Stock Exchange company, for nearly four years, including over two years as President and a member of the company’s Board of Directors. During his tenure at OCA, Geoff was responsible for the operations of the company and played a key role in building OCA’s infrastructure and driving significant growth. During this time, OCA completed numerous acquisitions, grew revenues in excess of 200% to nearly $250 million and net income nearly 200%.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prior to OCA, Geoff spent fifteen years with several major investment banking firms, including Drexel Burnham Lambert Incorporated, Bear Stearns &amp; Co., Inc., and Prudential Securities, Inc., providing merger &amp; acquisition and financing advice exclusively to middle and lower middle market companies. During his investment banking career, Geoff executed over 100 transactions accounting for over $6 billion in transaction value.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Geoff previously served on the boards of Orthodontic Centers of America, Coast Dental Services, Inc. / Intelident Solutions, Inc., and Sterling/AEC.</p>', 'Geoffrey L. Faux', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'geoffrey-l-faux', '', '', '2016-10-19 14:58:24', '2016-10-19 14:58:24', '', 0, 'http://caymuspartners.com/wordpress/?post_type=our_team&#038;p=153', 0, 'our_team', '', 0),
