(516, 1, '2013-10-29 15:43:31', '2013-10-29 15:43:31', '<p>Michael P.Howell, a Managing Partner of Caymus Equity, has over 30 years of investing, senior executive, and financial experience focused on the lower middle market. Mr. Howell has spent most of his career starting, acquiring, operating, growing, and successfully exiting a variety of lower middle market businesses. Mr. Howell’s expertise includes developing and executing strategic plans, building infrastructure, attracting senior executives, and leading companies to achieve their growth plans.</p>\n\n<p>Mr. Howell joined Caymus Equity Partners in March 2012. Given his deep lower middle market operating and investing experience, Mr. Howell brings a unique skill set to Caymus Equity Partners. Mr. Howell’s extensive operating and financial experience is instrumental in assisting the executive management teams of Caymus Equity Partners’ portfolio companies navigate critical decisions to achieve their growth goals. Mr. Howell is active in deal generation and transaction consummation.</p>\n\n<p>In 2001, Mr. Howell was the founder, Chairman, and Chief Executive Officer of ReachOut Healthcare America (“RHA”), a provider of mobile dental services to schools, nursing homes, and military installations. As Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of RHA, Mr. Howell developed, led, and executed its strategic plan of providing critical dental services to a variety of patients in need. RHA rapidly became one of the largest providers of pediatric dental services in the nation under Mr. Howell’s leadership. By November 2007, Mr. Howell and his team completed a majority recapitalization with Sentinel Capital Partners. Mr. Howell remained as the Chief Executive Officer, and was responsible for the continued rapid growth of the company over the next three years, with expansion into the military and nursing home sectors. From 2007 through 2010, Mr. Howell led the organic growth of RHA and executed the successful acquisition and subsequent integration of RHA’s two largest competitors. In December 2010, RHA was successfully sold to Morgan Stanley Capital Partners, and Mr. Howell continues as Vice Chairman. Today, RHA provides mobile dental services in 9,000 schools, nursing homes, and military installations in 31 states.</p>\n\n<p>Prior to ReachOut Healthcare America, Mr. Howell owned and operated a variety of companies in the automotive sector, with a focus on retailing, manufacturing, importing, and wholesale distribution of cars and automotive parts in Michigan, New York, and California. In addition, he was a member of the founding team and board of directors of American Dental Laser (“ADL”). ADL developed, manufactured, and distributed the first laser used in dentistry and Mr. Howell was responsible for the development of a two-tier distribution network in 31 countries. Mr. Howell began his career in the audit department of Deloitte Touche.</p>\n', 'Michael P. Howell', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '149-autosave-v1', '', '', '2013-10-29 15:43:31', '2013-10-29 15:43:31', '', 149, 'http://caymusequity.com/149-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(517, 1, '2013-09-24 21:29:47', '2013-09-24 21:29:47', '<h5>Content</h5>\n<p>This website is intended solely to provide information regarding Caymus Equity\'s potential financing capabilities for prospective portfolio investments.</p>\n<p>Nothing on this website constitutes or forms a part of any offer for sale or subscription of, or any invitation to offer to buy or subscribe for, any securities, nor should it or any part of it form the basis of, or be relied upon in any connection with any contract or commitment whatsoever.</p>\n<p>The information provided herein, including any information regarding Caymus Equity\'s current and historical portfolio investments, is not intended to recommend any investment described herein, and is not an offer or sale of any security or investment product or investment advice.</p>\n<p>Past performance is no guarantee of future results; there can be no assurance that similar opportunities will be available for the prospective investors or that the prospective investors will achieve similar investment results.</p>\n<h5>Links</h5>\n<p>The website may contain links to third party websites, including websites of entities affiliated with Caymus Equity or its principals’ predecessors’ investments.</p>\n<p>Caymus Equity provides these links for your convenience only, and makes no representation or warranty with respect to the content of the websites, the owners of the sites, or their products or services.</p>\n<p>Use of these third party sites is subject to the terms and conditions posted to the third party website.</p>\n', 'Terms and Conditions', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '41-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-24 21:29:47', '2013-09-24 21:29:47', '', 41, 'http://caymusequity.com/41-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(520, 1, '2016-12-29 23:58:13', '2016-12-29 23:58:13', '  <p>We seek to partner with excellent entrepreneurial management teams that are believed to be of high integrity and who have a compelling business strategy, a well-developed framework for implementing their strategy, a sustainable and scalable business model and platform, extensive industry and operating experience, and an established record of performance.</p>\n  <h5>Industry Focus</h5>\n  <div class="row" id="industry-focus">\n  <span class="span3">\n    <h5><img src="<?php bloginfo(\'template_directory\'); ?>/img/icon_business.gif">Business Services</h5>\n    <p>Service providers that leverage technology, information assets or a unique business process or strategy to deliver value to their customers.</p>\n  </span>\n  <span class="span3">\n    <h5><img src="<?php bloginfo(\'template_directory\'); ?>/img/icon_health.jpg">Healthcare Services</h5>\n    <p>Healthcare services companies with an established customer base and a scalable business. We avoid medical devices and biotechnology.</p>\n  </span>\n  <span class="span3">\n    <h5><img src="<?php bloginfo(\'template_directory\'); ?>/img/icon_consumer.jpg">Consumer</h5>\n    <p>Manufacturers of consumer oriented products and consumer services companies that compete in markets that are well established and not typically subject to the risks associated with economic cycles and technological obsolescence.</p>\n  </span>\n  <span class="span3">\n    <h5><img src="<?php bloginfo(\'template_directory\'); ?>/img/icon_niche.jpg">Niche Manufacturing</h5>\n    <p>Manufacturers that develop or reposition products and services in a way that adds value to a distinct customer base.</p>\n  </span>\n</div>\n<div class="row" id="industry-focus-2">\n<span class="span6 text">\n  <h5>Financial Criteria:</h5>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Targeted valuation of $10 million to $100 million</li>\n    <li>Revenue:  $10 million to $100 million</li>\n    <li>EBITDA:  $2 million to $12 million</li>\n    <li>Strong free cash flow</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h5>Prospect for Value Creation:</h5>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Organic growth</li>\n    <li>Ability to access new markets</li>\n    <li>Ability to broaden product or service offerings</li>\n    <li>Strategic acquisitions</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h5>Market Impact:</h5>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Differentiated or proprietary product, service, distribution channel,\n   process, or technology</li>\n    <li>Meaningful cost advantage and/or high switching costs</li>\n    <li>Strong customer base</li>\n    <li>High barriers to entry</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h5>Management:</h5>\n  <p>Strong management teams interested in partnering with Caymus Equity post-transaction, to take their companies to the next level</p>\n</span>\n<span class="span6 image">\n  <img src="<?php bloginfo(\'template_directory\'); ?>/img/lookfor_img1.jpg">\n</span>\n</div> ', 'What We Look For', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-12-29 23:58:13', '2016-12-29 23:58:13', '', 6, 'http://caymusequity.com/6-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
